---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { isBlogPublished } from '../../lib/blogGate';
import BlogCrossLinks from '../../components/BlogCrossLinks.astro';

const slug = Astro.url.pathname.replace('/blog/', '').replace(/\/$/, '');
const isPublished = await isBlogPublished(slug);
if (!isPublished) return Astro.redirect('/404');
---

<Layout title="Baby Weight: lbs to kg Conversion for New Parents" description="Baby weight conversion chart — lbs to kg. Quick reference for new parents to understand newborn weight in both units." keywords="baby weight conversion, lbs to kg baby, newborn weight chart, infant weight, baby weight kg to lbs, pediatric weight, baby growth chart">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-amber-600">Blog</a> <span class="mx-1">›</span> <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Weight</span>
      </nav>
      <BlogCrossLinks title="Baby Weight: lbs to kg Conversion for New Parents" />
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">June 8, 2025 • 4 min read</p>

      <p>When your baby is born, one of the first things you will hear is their weight. Depending on where you live, it might be announced in pounds and ounces or in kilograms. Here is a clear guide to help new parents understand baby weights in both systems.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">The Conversion Formula</h2>
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl p-5 my-6 not-prose">
        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono font-bold text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-400">1 lb = 0.4536 kg | 1 kg = 2.2046 lbs</p>
        <p class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mt-2">Remember: 1 oz = 28.35 g (there are 16 oz in 1 lb)</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Newborn Weight Reference Chart</h2>
      <p>Here are common newborn weights converted between systems:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>5 lbs 8 oz = 2.49 kg</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>6 lbs 0 oz = 2.72 kg</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>6 lbs 8 oz = 2.95 kg</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>7 lbs 0 oz = 3.18 kg</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>7 lbs 8 oz = 3.40 kg</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>8 lbs 0 oz = 3.63 kg</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>8 lbs 8 oz = 3.86 kg</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>9 lbs 0 oz = 4.08 kg</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>9 lbs 8 oz = 4.31 kg</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span>10 lbs 0 oz = 4.54 kg</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Average Newborn Weights</h2>
      <p>According to the World Health Organisation, the average full-term newborn weighs:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Girls:</strong> 3.2 kg (7 lbs 1 oz)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Boys:</strong> 3.3 kg (7 lbs 4 oz)</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Normal range:</strong> 2.5 to 4.5 kg (5 lbs 8 oz to 9 lbs 15 oz)</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Converting Pounds and Ounces to Kilograms</h2>
      <p>Baby weights in the US are expressed in pounds and ounces (e.g., "7 lbs 6 oz"). To convert this to kilograms:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Convert everything to ounces: (7 × 16) + 6 = 118 oz</li>
        <li>Multiply by 28.35 to get grams: 118 × 28.35 = 3,345 g</li>
        <li>Divide by 1000 to get kilograms: 3.35 kg</li>
      </ol>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-1">Why It Matters</h2>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Medical records</strong> — paediatricians track growth in the metric system for WHO growth charts</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Medicine dosing</strong> — infant medications are dosed per kilogram of body weight</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>International families</strong> — grandparents abroad may only understand one system</span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span>
          <span><strong>Growth percentiles</strong> — growth charts use kilograms, so you need accurate conversions</span>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>Tracking your baby's weight gain is one of the best indicators of healthy development in the first year. Whether your doctor uses kg or lbs, now you can understand both.</p>

      <div class="border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-800 mt-10 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Try It Now</h3>
        <a href="/convert/weight" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-amber-500 text-white text-sm font-semibold hover:bg-amber-600 transition-colors">Open Weight Converter →</a>
      </div>
    
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 p-4 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-800 rounded-xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 font-medium">🔗 Try our converter: <a href="/convert/weight" class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 font-bold hover:underline">Open Converter →</a></p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>
